In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders discussed the upcoming release of legislation based on the tax reform framework supported by President Trump. She criticized Democrats for their expected opposition to the tax cuts and highlighted the historical support for cutting corporate tax rates from both Democratic and Republican leaders. Sanders also addressed questions about the investigation into Russian interference in the 2016 election, stating that the Trump campaign did not collude with Russia. She defended Chief of Staff John Kelly's comments about the Civil War, stating that history cannot be erased or rewritten. Sanders also mentioned that the President is not considering defunding the special counsel and expressed confidence that the investigation will wrap up soon. She declined to comment on Facebook's disclosure of Russian propaganda and referred questions to the social media company. Sanders also mentioned that the President supports the child tax credit and does not believe the Obamacare individual mandate needs to be part of tax reform.